                            <comment id="15943322" author="knoguchi" created="Mon, 27 Mar 2017 14:07:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hanging itself is same from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-4976&quot; title=&quot;streaming job with store clause stuck if the script fail&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-4976&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-4976&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, but unlike that jira, here POStream is properly returning &lt;tt&gt;POStatus.STATUS_ERR&lt;/tt&gt;.  It&apos;s just that POSplit is converting that to RESULT_EMPTY.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;POSplit.java&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;244         &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; (res.returnStatus == POStatus.STATUS_OK) ? res : RESULT_EMPTY;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attaching a patch that would return STATUS_ERR in such cases.&lt;br/&gt;
I couldn&apos;t reproduce this on a small local unit test.  &lt;br/&gt;
Reason was when input is too small &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;POSplit.java&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;198     &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; Result getNextTuple() &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; ExecException {
199
200         &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.parentPlan.endOfAllInput) {
201
202             &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; getStreamCloseResult();
203
204         }
205
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This &lt;tt&gt;endOfAllInput&lt;/tt&gt; becomes true and code flow chooses a different path and does not hit this bug.  For now, added e2e test that produces the hang.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
